                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d495">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 838.00/1085.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Minister <persName type="from">Blanchard</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Port au Prince</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-01-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 20, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Consul at Gonaives reports that Saint Michel, Ennery, Limbe, Plaisance and other
                    surrounding places have taken up arms against the Government. It is reported
                    that Vilbrun Guillaume has proclaimed himself chief of the disaffections at Cape
                    Haitien.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Blanchard</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
